Configuring Community Profiles for OmniScript

To allow deployment of an OmniScript from an Experience page, configure the following sharing settings and profile access.

Beginning with the Winter '20 Salesforce release, Guest Users cannot access any records by default. Vlocity allows guest users to create and update the records to which Sharing Rules grant access.

To configure sharing settings:

* From Setup, click Security Controls or Security and then click Sharing Settings.
* Set the Default Internal Access and External Default Access for Vlocity OmniScript to Public Read Only.
* If writing to the Application object, set the Default Internal Access and Default External Access to Public Read/Write.
* Click Save.

The prerequisite for these steps is that communities must exist in your org.

To configure community user visibility:

* From Setup, click Customize or Feature Settings, then click Communities, then click All Communities.
* Make sure all profiles that should access the community are selected, then click Save.

To set field-level security:

* From Setup, click Manage Users or Users, then click Profiles.
* Find the profile for the users who will be accessing the community and click its name.
* Scroll down to the Field Level Security section and click View next to Application.
* Click Edit and click Read Access next to every field.
* Click Save.

Setting Object Permissions and Enabling APIs, Visualforce Pages, and Apex Access

Vlocity allows guest users to create and update the records to which Sharing Rules grant access. No additional configuration is necessary for this expanded access.
